.TH "uv_mmtimer_ioctl" 9 "uv_mmtimer_ioctl" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
uv_mmtimer_ioctl \- ioctl interface for /dev/uv_mmtimer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" uv_mmtimer_ioctl
.BI "(struct file *file "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cmd "  ","
.BI "unsigned long arg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "file" 12
file structure for the device
.IP "cmd" 12
command to execute
.IP "arg" 12
optional argument to command
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Executes the command specified by \fIcmd\fP.  Returns 0 for success, < 0 for
failure.

Valid commands:

MMTIMER_GETOFFSET - Should return the offset (relative to the start
of the page where the registers are mapped) for the counter in question.

MMTIMER_GETRES - Returns the resolution of the clock in femto (10^-15)
seconds

MMTIMER_GETFREQ - Copies the frequency of the clock in Hz to the address
specified by \fIarg\fP

MMTIMER_GETBITS - Returns the number of bits in the clock's counter

MMTIMER_MMAPAVAIL - Returns 1 if registers can be mmap'd into userspace

MMTIMER_GETCOUNTER - Gets the current value in the counter and places it
in the address specified by \fIarg\fP.
